{
  "texts": [
    "As defined, the meaning of 'environmental learning' overlaps with the meaning of 'social learning'.",
    "That is, the two are not independently defined.",
    "This entails that 'environmental learning' could also be modelled to yield S-shaped curves.",
    "This appears inconsistent with Henrich's conclusions from the model.",
    "If the definitions of 'social learning' and 'environmental learning' are not retooled, subsequent modelling and experimentation using these definitions are unlikely to overcome challenge (C3)."
  ]
}